  "response_text": "The reserve biomass begins at approximately 90,000 units. During the initial 5 time steps, the metric remains stable or experiences a marginal increase to roughly 90,500–91,000 units. A pronounced decline phase follows, with biomass decreasing steadily over the subsequent 35 time steps. By time step 40, the system reaches minimum values ranging between 80,000 and 95,000 units across different simulation runs. Most trajectories bottom out between 80,000 and 85,000 units, though select runs maintain higher biomass levels approaching 90,000–95,000 units during this period.

